<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,370,836]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,271,370,396]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Species of medium to small size (
<quantity box="[707,858,370,396]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.65" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="4.65" valueMax="5.8" valueMin="3.5">3.5–5.8 mm</quantity>
), very similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1072,1221,370,395]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomeira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gougeletii">
<emphasis box="[1072,1221,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">P. gougeletii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but easily distinguished from it, apart from the characters in the key also by the rostrum being longer than wide, the less robust funicle, the more elongate and convex eyes and the different outline of the pre-apical part of the aedeagus. Apex of aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[485,583,490,516]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–25. 24" captionStartId="64.[151,269,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[203,1384,158,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-53@64.[195,1391,149,1964]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURES 24–25. 24. Pseudomeira alonsoi: a. apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; b. endophallic structures. 25. Pseudomeira baetica: a. apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; b. endophallic structures. Scale: 0.15 mm; 0.10 mm (b)." pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 24a</figureCitation>
, endophallic structures as in 
<figureCitation box="[922,1023,490,516]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–25. 24" captionStartId="64.[151,269,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[203,1384,158,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-53@64.[195,1391,149,1964]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURES 24–25. 24. Pseudomeira alonsoi: a. apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; b. endophallic structures. 25. Pseudomeira baetica: a. apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; b. endophallic structures. Scale: 0.15 mm; 0.10 mm (b)." pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 24b</figureCitation>
; spermatheca as in 
<figureCitation box="[1250,1350,490,516]" captionStart="FIGURE 52" captionStartId="79.[151,255,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[242,1343,205,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-37@79.[234,1353,194,1783]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURE 52. Spermatheca: a. Pseudomeira alonsoi; b. P. baetica; c. P. eremita; d. P.lepida. Scale: 0.10 mm." pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 52a</figureCitation>
. Specimens from the province of Sevilla have a shorter rostrum with subparallel sides and a more robust funicle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
